{
  "filename": "CHECK_N_019_STEERING_GEAR_TEST_PRIOR_DEPARTURE_(LAMINATED).docx",
  "doc_type": "Checklist",
  "title": "N 019 - Steering Gear Tests Prior Departure",
  "sections": [
    {
      "name": "A. NAVIGATION OFFICER",
      "content": "1. Bridge remote steering control systems\n2. Steering positions on the bridge\n3. Steering gear power units change-over\n4. Steering gear power unit failure alarms (alarm panel)\n5. Helm and rudder angle indicators\n6. Rudder angle indicators in relation to actual rudder position\n7. Communication system between bridge and steering gear compartment (electrical and em’cy powered telephones)\n8. Full movement of the rudder according to steering gear capabilities (with main and emergency system use)\n9. Check the timing of rudder movement from hard-over to hard-over, using each steering gear power unit singly and together (Time hard-over to hard-over with one power unit           sec and two power units           sec)\n10. Compass in steering gear room\n11. Simple operating instructions with a block diagram showing change-over procedures for remote st. gear control systems displayed on bridge and in the steering gear compartment"
    },
    {
      "name": "B. CHIEF ENGINEER",
      "content": "1. Main steering gear unit\n2. Auxiliary steering gear unit or rudder arrester gear\n3. Remote steering gear control system\n4. Emergency power supply\n5. Visual inspection of st. gear and its connecting linkages\n6. Visual verification of hydraulic oil level in system\n7. Rudder carrier bearing and bottom sea gland\n8. Smooth pumps operation\n9. Absence of abnormal noise and heat"
    },
    {
      "name": "C. ETO",
      "content": "1. Steering gear power unit failure alarms\n2. Automatic isolating arrangements, other automatic equipment\n3. Remote steering gear control systems power failure alarms\n4. Hydraulic oil service tank low and low-low alarms"
    }
  ],
  "category": "Navigation",
  "form_number": "N 019",
  "normalized_topic": "Steering Gear Test",
